[SN]TITLE[SN]
Boy, 11, critical after hit by motorbike in Mountain Ash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An 11-year-old boy is in a critical condition in hospital after being hit by a motorcyclist who left the scene of the incident in Rhondda Cynon Taff.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
South Wales Police said the "serious road traffic collision" at Penrhiwceiber Road, Mountain Ash, happened at 08:45 BST on Thursday.
The boy was flown to Cardiff's University Hospital of Wales by air ambulance.
Police are trying to trace the rider of the red motorbike.
